site_name: Redevelopment site at Wornington Green Estate: Land north of Athlone Gardens/Murchison Gardens between the Barlby Road junction, railway line and Ladbroke Grove, including Wornington Road and Portobello Road, LONDON, W10 5LR
description: ***Amended description*** Demolition of existing buildings/structures to enable redevelopment of the site (Phase 3) with six blocks ranging from 4 to 15 storeys in height to provide between 368 and 370 residential dwellings (Use Class C3), with ground floor commercial space (Use Class E) and flexible community / commercial space (Use Class E/F.1/F.2); provision of a community centre with associated adventure playground (Use Class F.1/F.2) including up to 760 sq.m flexible floorspace including steel pan workshop (Use Class E/F.1/F.2), along with a community kitchen garden at roof level; and car and cycle parking, landscaping and public realm improvements. ***(Amendments include: internal alterations to building layouts and revised housing size mix resulting in an overall reduction from 373 - 377 homes to 368 - 370 homes, and increased number of larger wheelchair user homes; increased height and revised rear fa‡ade of Blocks 5 and 10; revised highway layout to prevent access from Wornington Road to Ladbroke Grove / Barlby Road roundabout, and car parking, cycle parking and servicing changes; revised public realm and landscaping including retention of an additional tree and increased planting of new trees; introduction of a second staircase in Block 9A; changes to the ground floor floorspace, layout and arrangement of commercial and community uses in parts of Blocks 7, 8 and 10; and revisions to environmental sustainability details.Further amendments and information include: changes to highways site layout and public realm including reduction in car parking provision, changes to long-stay cycle parking in each block, and additional windows to Block 9B studio flats at fourth and fifth floor levels; provision of Phasing Plan; and changes / updates to technical matters relating to drainage, trees, biodiversity, air quality, noise, energy and sustainability, fire safety, residential quality, financial viability, and the Environmental Statement and Environmental Implications Letter, as set out in revised drawings and technical reports)***[APPLICATION ACCOMPANIED BY AN ENVIRONMENTAL STATEMENT FOR THE PURPOSES OF ENVIRONMENTAL IMPACT ASSESSMENT; MAJOR DEVELOPMENT; AND DEVELOPMENT AFFECTING THE SETTING OF CONSERVATION AREAS AND THE SETTING OF LISTED BUILDINGS]A request for a hard copy of the Environmental Statement and Environmental Implications Letter can be made to CBRE to Ben Weldin-Berry (Ben.WeldinBerry@cbre.com, 07788 753 683) and Rebecca Raby Smith (Rebecca.Rabysmith@cbre.com, 07886 756 105).ÿ Please quote the reference 'Wornington Green Estate - Phase 3 EIA'.ÿ The approximate cost of a printed hard copy of the Environmental Statement is œ1,350 per copy (including delivery cost).
